 sauté <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Add corn kernels, stock paste, water and miso paste and cook <b>10 min\/120°C\/speed 4<b>. Blend <b>1 min\/speed 4<b><strong>-9, increasing speed gradually from speed 4 to speed 9<\/strong>. Serve corn purée dotted with almond ricotta, roasted pepper strips (optional) and garnish with fresh coriander (optional)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If you don't have time to soak\/activate your almonds, soak nuts in boiling water for 30 minutes, then drain and use as directed.","With a cheesy, umami flavour, nutritional yeast contains all nine essential amino acids, is a great source of B vitamins and is often fortified with vitamin B12 (important for those following a vegan diet). You can find nutritional yeast at health food stores or online.","You can store the Almond ricotta in the refrigerator for up to 2 days.","You can serve this dish as a side or as a dip with chips or crackers. We served it with our Vegan parmesan shards (refer to the recipe on this recipe chip)."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","3h 20m","4 portions"]}